# Backend Change Governance Rules

## API And Contract Changes

- Treat API and event contract changes as compatibility-sensitive by default.
- Mark breaking changes explicitly and provide migration guidance.
- Keep contract evolution incremental when feasible.

## Data And Migration Discipline

- Plan database/schema changes with rollout and rollback in mind.
- Avoid destructive migrations without a safe transition path.
- Verify migration impact on performance and data integrity.

## Dependency And Configuration

- Add backend dependencies only with clear value and ownership.
- Keep service configuration in environment/config sources, not hardcoded.
- Document operational impact of dependency or config changes.
